showing up in town and looking for a place to sleep, it's best to arrive before 6pm-7pm. or the most popular places will be booked for the night. note that if you are absolutely at a loss for finding housing, you should seek out the local police (警察) or public security bureau (公安局). they can help you find a place to crash - at least for one night. prices are often negotiable, and a sharp reduction from the price listed on the wall can often be had, even in nicer hotels, by simpy asking "what's the lowest price?" (最低多少 zuìdī 